Author: mdemare
Content:
Me too, I think by now Yahoo search is about as good as Google, for some things even a lot better. It's their ads that are much worse.

Google docs is a gamble that may or may not pay off, but it's not making them any (significant) money.

Yahoo does feel very unfocused. That's probably a bad sign.

Author: anewaccountname
Content:
More Greenspun hyperbole:

"Google unseated Yahoo at a cost of about $20 million in financing"

That completely ignores major things such as, oh I don't know, the Google Pagerank patent. It isn't like Google just won on simple UI; if their search hadn't worked way better than anything else, they never would have taken off.
